						               													<description>Mormon Trek is a simple roll-and-move designed to promote family discussion about the Mormon Pioneers experiences. Each game piece is a rocking chair that is being carried across the plains in wagon trains. Movement is dictated by die-roll with a custom dice featuring wagons, blessings, and tribulations. A wagon roll simple allows you to move forward. A blessing roll (golden key) lets you move to a special section of the board where you talk about blessings the pioneers experienced. A tribulation roll moves you backwards and requires you to talk about a trial the pioneers experienced.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to successfully travel from Nauvoo, IL to Salt Lake City, UT is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
